# Design Doc: XML Schema Bootstrapper for Profile Stat Groups (.NET 8.0)

## Overview

This document describes the design for porting the `XMLToAvroBootstrapperForProfileStatGroups` Python tool to C# .NET 8.0. The tool reads a leaderboard XML config file, converts it into a target schema format, and optionally registers those schemas against a Confluent Schema Registry.

The C# implementation generalises beyond Avro — the bootstrapper supports **Avro, JSON Schema, and Protobuf** as output formats, selected at runtime via configuration. Schema Registry API clients already exist in the codebase and will be called directly.

-----

## Functional Requirements

### Inputs

The tool accepts the following runtime inputs, provided via command-line arguments or a configuration object:

|Parameter            |Description                                                                   |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`env`                |Deployment environment (e.g., `dev`, `prod`)                                  |
|`title`              |Game title identifier (e.g., `hgt`, `rdr2`)                                   |
|`subject`            |Kafka subject prefix (env and title are appended at runtime)                  |
|`schemaFile`         |Filename of the XML config (must be in same directory as executable)          |
|`registryUrl`        |URL of the Confluent Schema Registry                                          |
|`updateRegistry`     |Boolean flag; if true, schemas are pushed to registry. If false, dry-run only.|
|`serializationFormat`|Target schema format: `Avro`, `Json`, or `Protobuf`                           |

The XML config file follows the `LeaderboardsConfiguration` schema, containing `StatGroups`, `Inputs`, `Categories`, and `CategoryPermutations` sections.

### Outputs

- One schema is generated per `StatGroup` found in the XML, in the chosen serialization format.
- All schemas are written to a local file: `{subject}_schema.{ext}` where `ext` is `json` (Avro/JSON Schema) or `proto` (Protobuf).
- If `updateRegistry` is true, each schema is registered to the Schema Registry under the subject: `{subject}-{statGroupName}-value`.
- The schema type passed to the registry (`AVRO`, `JSON`, `PROTOBUF`) is determined by the selected format.
- Console output is produced at each major step for observability.

### Dry Run Mode

When `updateRegistry` is false, the tool builds and writes schemas locally but does not call the Schema Registry. This is the default safe mode.

