### Interfaces

#### `IXmlParser`

Responsible for reading the XML config file and converting it into a structured `Dictionary<string, object>` representation, equivalent to the Python `convert_xml_to_dict` / `convert_xml_to_json` logic.

```csharp
public interface IXmlParser
{
    Dictionary<string, object> ParseFile(string filePath);
    Dictionary<string, object> ParseString(string xmlContent);
}
```

-----

#### `ITypeMapper`

Maps SQL/primitive type strings to their corresponding target-format type representation. Each serialization format has its own concrete implementation.

```csharp
public interface ITypeMapper
{
    // Returns a format-specific type token.
    // e.g. for Avro: "string", {"type":"long","logicalType":"timestamp-millis"}
    // for JSON Schema: "string", "integer", "number"
    // for Protobuf: "string", "int32", "int64", "double", "bool"
    object GetTypeForSqlType(string sqlType);

    SerializationFormat Format { get; }
}
```

Concrete implementations:

- `AvroTypeMapper` — returns Avro primitive types and logical type objects.
- `JsonTypeMapper` — returns JSON Schema type strings.
- `ProtobufTypeMapper` — returns Protobuf scalar type strings.

-----

#### `ISchemaBuilder`

Core interface for building schemas from parsed XML data. Each serialization format has its own concrete implementation. All builders consume the same format-neutral `Dictionary<string, object>` input and produce a list of `BuiltSchema` objects.

```csharp
public interface ISchemaBuilder
{
    SerializationFormat Format { get; }
    List<BuiltSchema> BuildSchemas(Dictionary<string, object> parsedXml, string title);
}
```

Concrete implementations:

- `AvroSchemaBuilder` — produces Avro record schemas serialized as JSON.
- `JsonSchemaBuilder` — produces JSON Schema (`$schema`, `properties`, `required`, etc.) serialized as JSON.
- `ProtobufSchemaBuilder` — produces `.proto` syntax 3 message definitions as a string.

Each builder internally handles:

- `GetBaseFields()` — returns the fixed base fields (handle, tag, time, guid, accountId, etc.) in its own format.
- `BuildCategories()` — resolves `CategoryPermutations` into format-specific field definitions.
- `BuildInputs()` — resolves `Columns` into input, aggregatedInputs, and aggregatedValues fields.
- `ProcessStatGroup()` — assembles the full schema for one stat group.

These remain internal to each concrete builder.

-----

#### `ISchemaBuilderFactory`

Resolves the correct `ISchemaBuilder` at runtime based on the configured `SerializationFormat`. This is the only place format-switching logic lives.

```csharp
public interface ISchemaBuilderFactory
{
    ISchemaBuilder GetBuilder(SerializationFormat format);
}
```

The concrete `SchemaBuilderFactory` receives all registered `ISchemaBuilder` implementations via DI and selects the matching one by `Format`.

-----

#### `ISchemaRegistrar`

Handles registration of compiled schemas to the Schema Registry. Format-aware: passes the correct schema type string (`AVRO`, `JSON`, `PROTOBUF`) when calling the existing registry client. No new HTTP logic is written here.

```csharp
public interface ISchemaRegistrar
{
    Task RegisterAsync(string subjectName, BuiltSchema schema);
    void PrintSchema(string subjectName, BuiltSchema schema);
}
```

-----

#### `IBootstrapperApp`

Top-level orchestrator interface. Wires together parsing, building, file writing, and registration.

```csharp
public interface IBootstrapperApp
{
    Task RunAsync();
}
```

The concrete `BootstrapperApp` takes all other interfaces via constructor injection. It:

1. Reads and parses the XML via `IXmlParser`.
1. Resolves the correct builder via `ISchemaBuilderFactory`.
1. Builds all schemas via `ISchemaBuilder`.
1. Writes schemas to disk.
1. Conditionally registers via `ISchemaRegistrar` based on `DryRun`.

-----

### Dependency Injection

All interfaces are registered in `Program.cs` using .NET 8.0’s built-in DI. All three builders and type mappers are registered so the factory can resolve any of them at runtime:

```csharp
var host = Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .ConfigureServices((ctx, services) =>
    {
        services.Configure<BootstrapperOptions>(ctx.Configuration);

        // XML parsing
        services.AddSingleton<IXmlParser, XmlParser>();

        // Type mappers — all registered, factory picks the right one
        services.AddSingleton<ITypeMapper, AvroTypeMapper>();
        services.AddSingleton<ITypeMapper, JsonTypeMapper>();
        services.AddSingleton<ITypeMapper, ProtobufTypeMapper>();

        // Schema builders — all registered, factory picks the right one
        services.AddSingleton<ISchemaBuilder, AvroSchemaBuilder>();
        services.AddSingleton<ISchemaBuilder, JsonSchemaBuilder>();
        services.AddSingleton<ISchemaBuilder, ProtobufSchemaBuilder>();

        services.AddSingleton<ISchemaBuilderFactory, SchemaBuilderFactory>();
        services.AddSingleton<ISchemaRegistrar, SchemaRegistrar>();
        services.AddSingleton<IBootstrapperApp, BootstrapperApp>();
    })
    .Build();

await host.Services.GetRequiredService<IBootstrapperApp>().RunAsync();
```

