## Format Behaviour Summary

|Concern              |Avro                                              |JSON Schema                             |Protobuf                   |
|---------------------|--------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|---------------------------|
|Field nullability    |`["null", type]` union                            |`type: [type, "null"]`                  |`optional` keyword         |
|Timestamp type       |`{"type":"long","logicalType":"timestamp-millis"}`|`{"type":"string","format":"date-time"}`|`google.protobuf.Timestamp`|
|Integer types        |`"int"` / `"long"`                                |`"integer"`                             |`int32` / `int64`          |
|Float/decimal        |`"double"`                                        |`"number"`                              |`double`                   |
|Registry type string |`AVRO`                                            |`JSON`                                  |`PROTOBUF`                 |
|Output file extension|`.json`                                           |`.json`                                 |`.proto`                   |

-----

## Key Behavioural Notes

- **Title-specific logic**: When `title == "rdr2"`, the stat group includes a hardcoded `posseInfo` record with an `id: long` field. This is handled inside `ProcessStatGroup` on each concrete builder.
- **Nullable fields**: All fields default to nullable across all formats, matching the Python Avro output behaviour.
- **`ISchemaBuilderFactory` is the only format switch**: No `if/switch` on format exists anywhere else in the codebase.
- **Schema Registry calls**: `SchemaRegistrar` calls the existing `ISchemaRegistryClient` already in the codebase. The only addition is passing the correct format type string per `BuiltSchema.Format`.

-----

## Out of Scope

- No changes to Schema Registry API clients.
- No XML schema validation (matches current Python behaviour).
- No support for complex nested Avro types beyond what the Python tool currently handles (tracked as a ToDo in the original).
- No runtime format conversion between Avro, JSON Schema, and Protobuf.
